## Context

Ticket 0115 delivered C2ST analytical null (PR #769).  Ticket 0124 covers L1.
This ticket covers S1 and S2, which require pairwise kernel/distance matrices
and are therefore O(N²) — the most complex of the four methods.

## Formulas

### S1 — MMD² (unbiased)
E(MMD²_unbiased | H₀) = 0 by construction.
Var(MMD²_unbiased | H₀) ≈ (4/n²) × Var[h(X,X')] under H₀
(Gretton 2012, Lemma 6).  Requires computing h(Xi,Xj) off-diagonal.

### S2 — energy distance
null_mean from mean of off-diagonal entries of pairwise Euclidean distance
matrix.
null_std from 4th-moment U-statistics (Székely & Rizzo 2013).  O(N²).

## Actions

1. Add `s1_analytical_null(K_pool)` and `s2_analytical_null(D_pool)` in
   `_permutation_accel.py` (where pairwise matrices are already computed for
   the MC path — reuse them).
2. Extend `compute_analytical_null.py` for `--method S1_MMD` and
   `--method S2_energy`.
3. Add Make targets in `zoo.mk`.
4. Pass `--analytical-null` to zoo figure recipes for S1 and S2.

## Constraint

The pairwise matrix for S1/S2 is O(N²) in memory.  For typical (year,window)
windows (~400 docs) this is ~1.3 MB per window — acceptable.  Use
`load_analysis_corpus(with_embeddings=True)` → `load_refined_embeddings()`.

## Test

Red: for Gaussian N(0,I_d) with n=200 iid samples, assert
s1_analytical_null returns null_mean ≈ 0 (within 1e-6).

